==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sennit
<hw>Sen"nit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Seven</ets> +
<ets>knit</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A braided
cord or fabric formed by plaiting together rope yarns or other small
stuff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Plaited straw or palm leaves for making
hats.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Senocular</ent>⟦br⟧
